The paper discusses the average case behavior of a sorting algorithm, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and algorithm analysis and complexity (cs.AL). The use of probability distributions and numerical approximations suggests information theory (cs.IT) may also be relevant. The computation of exact averages and experimental exploration of different insertion orders suggest numerical analysis (cs.NA) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) may also be relevant.
